(prosper Loan Data)¶

    by (Ahmed Aredah)

Project Describtion¶

Data Set¶

This data set contains 113,937 loans with 81 variables on each loan, including loan amount, borrower rate (or interest rate), current loan status, borrower income, and many others.

The data set is filtered to affecting variables only and records with NAN/NA values are deleted.

Project Output¶

In this explanatory study, we tend to study and address the following questions:

What factors affect a loans outcome status?

What affects the borrowers APR or interest rate?

Are there differences between loans depending on how large the original loan amount was?

In [14]:
# Convert days to years
def get_years_from_days(x, inverse = False):
    if x > 0:
        if not inverse:
            return x/360
        else:
            return x*360
        
# Convert Months to years
def get_years_from_months(x, inverse = False):
    if x > 0:
        if not inverse:
            return x/12
        else:
            return x*12
        
# Convert values to log10        
def apply_log10(x, inverse = False):
    if not inverse:
        return math.log(x,10)
    else:
        return 10**x
    
# Convert Values to log
def apply_log(x, inverse = False):
    if not inverse:
        return np.log(x)
    else:
        return np.exp(x)

#Convert values to 1/x
def div_inverse(x):
    if x == 0:
        return 0
    else:
        return 1/x
